name: Jeopardy! Masters
overview: The tournament features six former Jeopardy! champions competing round-robin style, with 10 hour-long episodes featuring 2 games each. Each of the 20 possible combinations of 6 players will be played, with all 6 players appearing in 1 game each episode.

episodes.name: Games 1 & 2
episodes.overview: Game 1: Amy Schneider, Matt Amodio, and Andrew He. Game 2: James Holzhauer, Mattea Roach, and Sam Buttrey.

episodes.name: Games 3 & 4
episodes.overview: Game 3: Sam Buttrey, Amy Schneider, and Mattea Roach. Game 4: Andrew He, James Holzhauer, and Matt Amodio.

episodes.name: Games 5 & 6
episodes.overview: Game 5: James Holzhauer, Amy Schneider, and Sam Buttrey. Game 6: Andrew He, Mattea Roach, and Matt Amodio.

episodes.name: Games 7 & 8
episodes.overview: Game 7: Andrew He, Sam Buttrey, and Amy Schneider. Game 8: James Holzhauer, Mattea Roach, and Matt Amodio.

episodes.name: Games 9 & 10
episodes.overview: Game 9: Mattea Roach, Matt Amodio, and Amy Schneider. Game 10: James Holzhauer, Andrew He, and Sam Buttrey.

episodes.name: Games 11 & 12
episodes.overview: Game 11: Andrew He, Mattea Roach, and Sam Buttrey. Game 12: James Holzhauer, Matt Amodio, and Amy Schneider.

episodes.name: Games 13 & 14
episodes.overview: Game 13: Mattea Roach, Matt Amodio, and Sam Buttrey. Game 14: James Holzhauer, Andrew He, and Amy Schneider.

episodes.name: Semifinals 1 & 2
episodes.overview: Semifinal 1: James Holzhauer, Andrew He, and Matt Amodio. Semifinal 2: James Holzhauer, Andrew He, and Mattea Roach.

episodes.name: Semifinals 3 & 4
episodes.overview: Semifinal 3: James Holzhauer, Mattea Roach, and Matt Amodio. Semifinal 4: Mattea Roach, Andrew He, and Matt Amodio.

episodes.name: The Finals
episodes.overview: James Holzhauer, Matt Amodio, and Mattea Roach play two final games to determine the winner.

episodes.name: Games 1 & 2
episodes.overview: Game 1: Mattea Roach, Matt Amodio, and Victoria Groce. Game 2: James Holzhauer, Yogesh Raut, and Amy Schneider.
